How do they know he's saying 'aye' and not 'I', for one?
附加记录：    

I was trying to write it in such a way that anyone reading this out loud would be forced to sound like a pirate. The syllables of 'Aye' and 'I' are different when you sound them out, so I played up the pirateness as much as possible in the interview. I can see why such a thing would break your immersion, especially since the Foundation is the one writing this Log. If more people say the same, I'll probably go ahead and fix it. And yes, I am aware that 'Aye' means 'yes' in .







